Canary Deployment (Complete Explanation):
------ ---------   ---------------------
Canary Deployment is a deployment strategy where you release a new version of an application to a small percentage of users first.
If everything works correctly,you gradually roll it out to everyone. If issues are found, 
you quickly roll back without affecting most users.

Why use Canary Deployment?

Imagine you have an application running:

Version 1 (Stable)
10 Pods
100% of users

You develop Version 2 with new features.

Instead of replacing all 10 pods immediately, you deploy only 1 pod with Version 2.

Version 1
9 Pods

Version 2
1 Pod

Only a small portion of traffic reaches Version 2.

If Version 2 has bugs:

Only a small number of users are affected.
You can roll back quickly.
The majority of users continue using Version 1.
